{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 09:32:02.832497", "event": "llm_end", "text": "I have submitted the final diagnosis.\n\nSummary of submission:\n- Anomaly detected: Yes\n- Faulty device(s): dns_server\n- Root cause: dns_service_down\n\nRationale:\n- DNS queries fail across the network and on the DNS server itself.\n- No process is listening on UDP/TCP port 53 on dns_server (10.200.0.2).\n- IP connectivity, OSPF routing, DHCP, and HTTP-by-IP are healthy, isolating the issue to the DNS service being down.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 1957, "output_tokens": 108, "total_tokens": 2065, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1792}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
